<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7300> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7300" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A son of L. Aelius Tubero (150); the famous jurisconsult to whom Dionysius of Halicarnassus dedicated his essay on Thucydides, husband of a daughter of Servius Sulpicius Rufus, with sons who attained the consulship in 11 and 4, respectively, he was almost certainly a senator before 31 (PIR(2) 1.25, no. 157, and 45, no. 274; De Laet, nos. 7 and 12; see W. Kunkel, Herkunft u. Sozialestellung der råmischen Juristen 37, no. 56).\n" .
